    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ 425\u00b0F/ Gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Cut the <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>halved potatoes </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-20 min or until fork tender</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/melty-raclette-topped-potatoes-with-winter-slaw/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim, then slice the<strong> spring onions </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/melty-raclette-topped-potatoes-with-winter-slaw/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> sliced spring onions</strong> to a large bowl with the<strong> pickled cabbage,</strong> <strong>mayo</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and give everything a really good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy winter slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/melty-raclette-topped-potatoes-with-winter-slaw/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>For fancy presentation, cut the <strong>peppered salami </strong>in half and roll each half into cone-shapes</p><p>Roll the<strong> Napoli salami</strong> into tubes and cut in half</p><p>Tip: Too fiddly? Just break both up into smaller pieces!</p><p>Tear the <strong>Serrano ham </strong>into smaller pieces and add to a serving board with the <strong>Napoli salami</strong> and<strong> salami cones </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> charcuterie</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/melty-raclette-topped-potatoes-with-winter-slaw/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> </strong>potatoes are fork tender, add them to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Bash the<strong> potatoes </strong>with a<strong> rolling pin</strong>, or crush them with a fork</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/melty-raclette-topped-potatoes-with-winter-slaw/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and top with the<strong> raclette cheese slices</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until the raclette is melted and starting to bubble around the edges</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/melty-raclette-topped-potatoes-with-winter-slaw/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> cornichons</strong> in half lengthways</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/melty-raclette-topped-potatoes-with-winter-slaw/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> raclette-topped potatoes</strong> with dollops of the <strong>creamy winter slaw</strong>, the <strong>charcuterie pieces</strong> and<strong> sliced cornichons</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Let everyone dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
